{"action": "edit", "code": "def main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    colors = get_colors(input_grid)\n    height, width = get_grey_rect_size(input_grid)\n    output_grid = np.zeros([height, width], dtype=np.int32)\n    output_grid.fill(grey)\n    output_grid = grey_rect.copy()\n    for i in range(output_grid.shape[0]):\n        output_grid[i, :] = colors[i]\n    return output_grid\ndef get_colors(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> List[int]:\n    colors = []\n    for color in np.unique(input_grid[0]):\n        if color not in [black, grey]:\n            colors.append(color)\n    return colors\ndef get_grey_rect_size(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> Tuple[int, int]:\n    grey_rect = np.where(input_grid == grey)\n    min_row, min_col = np.min(grey_rect, axis=1)\n    max_row, max_col = np.max(grey_rect, axis=1)\n    height = max_row - min_row + 1\n    width = max_col - min_col + 1\n    return (height, width)", "user_code": "def main(input_grid:np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    colors = `get the colors (except for black and grey) from 0th row to input_grid.shape[0] in the input_grid`(input_grid)\n    height, width = `Get the grey rect's height and width in the input_grid`(input_grid)\n    output_grid = np.zeros([height, width], dtype=np.int32)\n    output_grid.fill(grey)\n    output_grid = grey_rect.copy()\n    for i in range(output_grid.shape[0]):\n        output_grid[i, :] = colors[i]\n    return output_grid", "gpt_code": "def get_colors(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> List[int]:\n    colors = []\n    for color in np.unique(input_grid[0]):\n        if color not in [black, grey]:\n            colors.append(color)\n    return colors\ndef get_grey_rect_size(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> Tuple[int, int]:\n    grey_rect = np.where(input_grid == grey)\n    min_row, min_col = np.min(grey_rect, axis=1)\n    max_row, max_col = np.max(grey_rect, axis=1)\n    height = max_row - min_row + 1\n    width = max_col - min_col + 1\n    return (height, width)", "holes": {"get_colors": "get the colors (except for black and grey) from 0th row to input_grid.shape[0] in the input_grid", "get_grey_rect_size": "Get the grey rect's height and width in the input_grid"}}
